Small inconsistency: Removed generic Intent i and moved dependencies to ...

As commented by : @nelenkov on prior patch: https://github.com/AndlyticsProject/andlytics/pull/480
"Looks good, but can you please make this against the dev branch? We try not to touch master unless something in the API breaks. It will be merged into master in the next release."


As commented by : @nelenkov on prior patch: https://github.com/AndlyticsProject/andlytics/pull/479
"Thanks for the patch. However, I don't think this makes it more readable. Getting rid of the Intent i would be better IMHO. It's not like the switch just sets up the intent and it is started at the end of the method -- some cases use startActivity() and others startActivityForResult() so it is better each case to use an explicit, named intent."

title: Dropped support for API 7.
message:
Dropped support for API 7.
Removed API specific sync handlers.
Sync handlers and preferences deal in minutes and are only converted to seconds when needed.
Re-wrote how we manage auto sync to ensure we correctly show changes made via system settings. We track the sync period included disabled state, and the sync period excluding disabled state (i.e. last != 0 sync period). If all accounts are set not to sync via the sync handler, then syncing is disabled. If at least one account is set to sync, then syncing is enabled. When the user enables an account (LoginActivity), we enable syncing to match the master setting, when they disable the account, we disable syncing.

it uses hashCode() it'll override any notifications from the account
that are already there.

title: A basic implementation of JB notifications
message:
A basic implementation of JB notifications

All it really does now is show the normal text in a BigText, meaning that
if it's long and isn't fully readable you can expand it (on JB that is) to
read everything. It'll also show the account name it's for in the summary.
I also re-enabled the writing to the database so everyone can really test
this build without it not working properly. Note that this is just the
beginning, I'm planning on doing a lot more with this.

title: Added a loader in place of the refresh button as discussed in #141
message:
Added a loader in place of the refresh button as discussed in #141

This looks a lot better than the default infinite progressbar in ABS,
as it appears on the action item. This has a small downside when in
landscape though. As it can't show the text when it has an ActionView,
in some cases it'll have 'enough room' to show both the export and import
action items. Causing the account picker to be a tad smaller in some cases.
In my opinion the import and export shouldn't even be in the ActionBar as
they aren't exactly features a user uses a lot.

title: Added a new BaseDetailsActitity and moved all the code from BaseActivity that is…
message: Added a new BaseDetailsActitity and moved all the code from BaseActivity that is used in the details views (Comments, Downloads etc...) into the new activity. This also allowed some duplicated code from the CommentsActivity, AdmobActivity etc to be removed. LoginActivity no longer extends BaseActivity as it has no need to. I'm also using Utils.execute() for some tasks to avoid a delay on HC+ when switching accounts and when scrolling through apps during the initial load.
